### Planner Response

I see what's happening. The Apps Script Editor is still "caching" the old permissions state, so it runs the script thinking "I have everything I need!" and then fails when the code tries to use the new permission.

**The Solution:**
1.  **Refresh your browser tab** for the Google Apps Script editor. This is critical to force it to reload the permissions manifest.
2.  Select [debugAuth](cci:1://file:///Users/matthewmarshall/jsonprez/Server/Debug.gs:1:0-31:1) and click **Run** again.
3.  **Now** the popup should appear.

Let me know once you've successfully authorized it!

function setTheme(themeConfig) {
  if (!themeConfig) {
    CURRENT_THEME = DEFAULT_THEME;

  CURRENT_THEME = {

function resolveThemeColor(colorValue) {
  if (!colorValue) return null;
  if (colorValue.startsWith('#')) return colorValue;
  
  const theme = CURRENT_THEME || DEFAULT_THEME;
  return theme.colors[colorValue] || colorValue;
}

function resolveThemeFont(fontValue) {
  if (!fontValue) return CONFIG.DEFAULTS.FONT_FAMILY;
  
  const theme = CURRENT_THEME || DEFAULT_THEME;
  return theme.fonts[fontValue] || fontValue;
}

// ============================================================================
// PHASE 2 TRACKING SYSTEM (FIXED)
// ============================================================================

/**
 * Phase 2 Queue - Tracks operations that must happen after Phase 1
 * NOW WITH PROPER OBJECT ID TRACKING
 */
let phase2Queue = {
  charts: [],       // { slideIndex, chartSpec }
  speakerNotes: [], // { slideIndex, notes }
  groups: [],       // { slideIndex, elementIds: [] }
  
  // Element ID mapping: originalIndex -> objectId
  elementIds: {},   // { 'slide_0_element_5': 'obj_abc123' }
  
  reset: function() {
    this.charts = [];
    this.speakerNotes = [];
    this.groups = [];
    this.elementIds = {};
  },
  
  // Store element ID for later lookup
  recordElementId: function(slideIndex, elementIndex, objectId) {
    const key = `slide_${slideIndex}_element_${elementIndex}`;
    this.elementIds[key] = objectId;
    Logger.log(`Recorded: ${key} -> ${objectId}`);
  },
  
  // Get element ID
  getElementId: function(slideIndex, elementIndex) {
    const key = `slide_${slideIndex}_element_${elementIndex}`;
    return this.elementIds[key];
  }
};

// ============================================================================
// UTILITY FUNCTIONS
// ============================================================================

function generateObjectId() {
  const chars = 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789';
  let result = 'obj_';
  for (let i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
    result += chars.charAt(Math.floor(Math.random() * chars.length));
  }
  return result;
}

function normalizeProperties(obj) {
  if (!obj || typeof obj !== 'object') return obj;
  const normalized = {};
  for (let key in obj) {
    if (!obj.hasOwnProperty(key)) continue;
    const normalizedKey = CONFIG.PROPERTY_ALIASES[key] || key;
    normalized[normalizedKey] = obj[key];
  }
  return normalized;
}

function normalizeColor(color) {
  if (!color || color === 'none' || color === 'transparent') return null;
  if (!color.startsWith('#')) color = '#' + color;
  if (color.length === 4) {
    color = '#' + color[1] + color[1] + color[2] + color[2] + color[3] + color[3];
  }
  return color.toLowerCase();
}

function hexToRgbApi(hex) {
  hex = normalizeColor(hex);
  if (!hex) return null;
  const result = /^#?([a-f\d]{2})([a-f\d]{2})([a-f\d]{2})$/i.exec(hex);
  return result ? {
    red: parseInt(result[1], 16) / 255,
    green: parseInt(result[2], 16) / 255,
    blue: parseInt(result[3], 16) / 255
  } : null;
}

function transformCoordinates(x, y, w, h) {
  return {
    x: (x || 0) * SCALE,
    y: (y || 0) * SCALE,
    w: (w || 0) * SCALE,
    h: (h || 0) * SCALE
  };
}

function clamp(value, min, max) {
  return Math.max(min, Math.min(max, value));
}

// ============================================================================
// VALIDATION (NOW WITH CENTRALIZED THEME RESOLUTION)
// ============================================================================

/**
 * Validate and sanitize element - NOW RESOLVES ALL THEME VALUES HERE
 */
function validateElement(element) {
  if (!element || !element.type) {
    throw new Error('Element must have a type property');
  }

  element = normalizeProperties(element);

  // Validate dimensions
  if (element.w !== undefined) {
    element.w = clamp(element.w, CONFIG.LIMITS.MIN_DIMENSION, CONFIG.LIMITS.MAX_DIMENSION);
  }
  if (element.h !== undefined) {
    element.h = clamp(element.h, CONFIG.LIMITS.MIN_DIMENSION, CONFIG.LIMITS.MAX_DIMENSION);
  }

  // Validate font size
  if (element.fontSize) {
    element.fontSize = clamp(element.fontSize, CONFIG.LIMITS.MIN_FONT_SIZE, CONFIG.LIMITS.MAX_FONT_SIZE);
  }

  // Preserve original for transparent detection
  if (element.fillColor) {
    element._originalFillColor = element.fillColor;
  }

  // CENTRALIZED THEME RESOLUTION - happens once here
  if (element.color) element.color = normalizeColor(resolveThemeColor(element.color));
  if (element.fillColor) element.fillColor = normalizeColor(resolveThemeColor(element.fillColor));
  if (element.background) element.background = normalizeColor(resolveThemeColor(element.background));
  if (element.borderColor) element.borderColor = normalizeColor(resolveThemeColor(element.borderColor));
  if (element.fontFamily) element.fontFamily = resolveThemeFont(element.fontFamily);

  // Validate text length
  if (element.text && element.text.length > CONFIG.LIMITS.MAX_TEXT_LENGTH) {
    element.text = element.text.substring(0, CONFIG.LIMITS.MAX_TEXT_LENGTH) + '...';
  }

  return element;
}

function validateJSON(json) {
  if (!json || !json.slides || !Array.isArray(json.slides)) {
    throw new Error('JSON must have a slides array');
  }
  if (json.slides.length === 0) {
    throw new Error('Presentation must have at least one slide');
  }
  if (json.slides.length > CONFIG.LIMITS.MAX_SLIDES) {
    throw new Error(`Maximum ${CONFIG.LIMITS.MAX_SLIDES} slides allowed`);
  }
  json.slides.forEach((slide, index) => {
    if (slide.elements && slide.elements.length > CONFIG.LIMITS.MAX_ELEMENTS_PER_SLIDE) {
      throw new Error(`Slide ${index + 1} exceeds ${CONFIG.LIMITS.MAX_ELEMENTS_PER_SLIDE} elements`);
    }
  });
  return json;
}

// ============================================================================
// REQUEST BUILDERS - EXTRACTED HELPERS
// ============================================================================

function buildTransform(x, y, rotation, w, h) {
  const px = (x || 0) * SCALE;
  const py = (y || 0) * SCALE;
  const pw = (w || 100) * SCALE;
  const ph = (h || 100) * SCALE;

  if (!rotation || rotation === 0) {
    return {
      scaleX: 1, scaleY: 1, shearX: 0, shearY: 0,
      translateX: px, translateY: py, unit: 'PT'
    };
  }

  const radians = (rotation * Math.PI) / 180;
  const cos = Math.cos(radians);
  const sin = Math.sin(radians);
  const tx = px + (pw / 2) * (1 - cos) + (ph / 2) * sin;
  const ty = py + (ph / 2) * (1 - cos) - (pw / 2) * sin;

  return {
    scaleX: cos, scaleY: cos, shearX: -sin, shearY: sin,
    translateX: tx, translateY: ty, unit: 'PT'
  };
}

function buildSize(w, h) {
  const coords = transformCoordinates(0, 0, w, h);
  return {
    width: { magnitude: coords.w, unit: 'PT' },
    height: { magnitude: coords.h, unit: 'PT' }
  };
}

function buildLinkRequest(objectId, link, elementType) {
  if (!link) return null;

  let linkObj = {};
  if (typeof link === 'string') {
    linkObj.url = link;
  } else if (typeof link === 'object') {
    if (link.url) linkObj.url = link.url;
    else if (link.slideIndex !== undefined) linkObj.slideIndex = link.slideIndex;
    else if (link.relativeLink) linkObj.relativeLink = link.relativeLink.toUpperCase().replace(/-/g, '_');
    else if (link.slide !== undefined) linkObj.slideIndex = link.slide;
  }

  if (elementType === 'text') {
    return {
      updateTextStyle: {
        objectId: objectId,
        style: { link: linkObj },
        textRange: { type: 'ALL' },
        fields: 'link'
      }
    };
  } else if (elementType === 'shape') {
    return {
      updateShapeProperties: {
        objectId: objectId,
        shapeProperties: { link: linkObj },
        fields: 'link'
      }
    };
  }

  return null;
}

/**
 * Build fake shadow (semi-transparent shape behind element)
 * NOTE: This is a workaround - Slides API shadows are read-only
 */
function buildFakeShadowRequests(element, slideId, shapeType) {
  if (!element.shadow) return [];

  const requests = [];
  let shadowConfig;

  if (element.shadow === true) {
    shadowConfig = { ...CONFIG.SHADOW_PRESETS.medium };
  } else if (typeof element.shadow === 'string') {
    shadowConfig = { ...(CONFIG.SHADOW_PRESETS[element.shadow] || CONFIG.SHADOW_PRESETS.medium) };
  } else if (typeof element.shadow === 'object') {
    shadowConfig = { ...CONFIG.SHADOW_PRESETS.medium, ...element.shadow };
  } else {
    return [];
  }

  // Calculate offset from angle/distance
  let offsetX, offsetY;
  if (shadowConfig.angle !== undefined && shadowConfig.distance !== undefined) {
    const angleRad = (shadowConfig.angle * Math.PI) / 180;
    offsetX = shadowConfig.distance * Math.cos(angleRad);
    offsetY = shadowConfig.distance * Math.sin(angleRad);
  } else {
    offsetX = shadowConfig.offsetX !== undefined ? shadowConfig.offsetX : 5;
    offsetY = shadowConfig.offsetY !== undefined ? shadowConfig.offsetY : 5;
  }

  const spread = shadowConfig.spread !== undefined ? shadowConfig.spread :
                 shadowConfig.blur !== undefined ? shadowConfig.blur : 4;
  const opacity = shadowConfig.opacity !== undefined ? shadowConfig.opacity :
                  shadowConfig.alpha !== undefined ? shadowConfig.alpha : 0.15;

  let shadowColor = shadowConfig.color || '#000000';
  if (shadowColor === 'inherit') {
    shadowColor = element.fillColor || element.fill || element.background || '#3b82f6';
  }
  shadowColor = resolveThemeColor(shadowColor);
  const rgb = hexToRgbApi(normalizeColor(shadowColor));

  const x = (element.x || 0) * SCALE;
  const y = (element.y || 0) * SCALE;
  const w = (element.w || 100) * SCALE;
  const h = (element.h || 100) * SCALE;
  const scaledOffsetX = offsetX * SCALE;
  const scaledOffsetY = offsetY * SCALE;
  const scaledSpread = spread * SCALE;

  const shadowId = generateObjectId();
  const shadowW = w + scaledSpread;
  const shadowH = h + scaledSpread;
  const shadowX = x + scaledOffsetX - scaledSpread * 0.5;
  const shadowY = y + scaledOffsetY - scaledSpread * 0.5;

  requests.push({
    createShape: {
      objectId: shadowId,
      shapeType: shapeType || 'RECTANGLE',
      elementProperties: {
        pageObjectId: slideId,
        size: {
          width: { magnitude: shadowW, unit: 'PT' },
          height: { magnitude: shadowH, unit: 'PT' }
        },
        transform: {
          scaleX: 1, scaleY: 1, shearX: 0, shearY: 0,
          translateX: shadowX, translateY: shadowY, unit: 'PT'
        }
      }
    }
  });

  requests.push({
    updateShapeProperties: {
      objectId: shadowId,
      shapeProperties: {
        shapeBackgroundFill: {
          solidFill: {
            color: { rgbColor: rgb },
            alpha: opacity
          }
        },
        outline: { propertyState: 'NOT_RENDERED' }
      },
      fields: 'shapeBackgroundFill,outline'
    }
  });

  return requests;
}

// ============================================================================
// TEXT ELEMENT
// ============================================================================

function buildTextRequests(element, slideId) {
  element = validateElement(element);
  const requests = [];
  const shapeId = element.objectId || generateObjectId();

  // Shadow first (if background present)
  if (element.shadow && element.background) {
    requests.push(...buildFakeShadowRequests(element, slideId, 'RECTANGLE'));
  }

  // Create text box
  requests.push({
    createShape: {
      objectId: shapeId,
      shapeType: 'TEXT_BOX',
      elementProperties: {
        pageObjectId: slideId,
        size: buildSize(element.w || 200, element.h || 50),
        transform: buildTransform(element.x || 0, element.y || 0, element.rotation, element.w || 200, element.h || 50)
      }
    }
  });

  // Determine text content
  let textContent = element.text || '';
  if (element.items && Array.isArray(element.items)) {
    textContent = element.items.map(item => {
      if (typeof item === 'string') return item;
      if (typeof item === 'object' && item.text) {
        const indent = '\t'.repeat(item.indent || 0);
        return indent + item.text;
      }
      return String(item);
    }).join('\n');
  }

  if (textContent) {
    requests.push({
      insertText: {
        objectId: shapeId,
        text: textContent,
        insertionIndex: 0
      }
    });

    // Text style
    const textStyle = {};
    const fields = [];

    const fontSize = (element.fontSize || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.FONT_SIZE) * SCALE;
    textStyle.fontSize = { magnitude: fontSize, unit: 'PT' };
    fields.push('fontSize');

    textStyle.fontFamily = element.fontFamily || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.FONT_FAMILY;
    fields.push('fontFamily');

    const textColor = element.color || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.TEXT_COLOR;
    const rgb = hexToRgbApi(textColor);
    if (rgb) {
      textStyle.foregroundColor = { opaqueColor: { rgbColor: rgb } };
      fields.push('foregroundColor');
    }

    if (element.bold) { textStyle.bold = true; fields.push('bold'); }
    if (element.italic) { textStyle.italic = true; fields.push('italic'); }
    if (element.underline) { textStyle.underline = true; fields.push('underline'); }
    if (element.strikethrough) { textStyle.strikethrough = true; fields.push('strikethrough'); }
    if (element.smallCaps) { textStyle.smallCaps = true; fields.push('smallCaps'); }

    if (element.subscript) {
      textStyle.baselineOffset = 'SUBSCRIPT';
      fields.push('baselineOffset');
    } else if (element.superscript) {
      textStyle.baselineOffset = 'SUPERSCRIPT';
      fields.push('baselineOffset');
    }

    if (fields.length > 0) {
      requests.push({
        updateTextStyle: {
          objectId: shapeId,
          style: textStyle,
          textRange: { type: 'ALL' },
          fields: fields.join(',')
        }
      });
    }

    // Alignment
    if (element.align) {
      requests.push({
        updateParagraphStyle: {
          objectId: shapeId,
          style: { alignment: ALIGNMENT_MAP[element.align] || 'START' },
          textRange: { type: 'ALL' },
          fields: 'alignment'
        }
      });
    }

    // Hyperlink
    if (element.link) {
      const linkRequest = buildLinkRequest(shapeId, element.link, 'text');
      if (linkRequest) requests.push(linkRequest);
    }

    // Lists/bullets
    if (element.list) {
      const listType = typeof element.list === 'string' ? element.list : 'bullet';
      const bulletPreset = CONFIG.LIST_PRESETS[listType] || CONFIG.LIST_PRESETS['bullet'];
      requests.push({
        createParagraphBullets: {
          objectId: shapeId,
          bulletPreset: bulletPreset,
          textRange: { type: 'ALL' }
        }
      });
    }
  }

  return { requests, objectId: shapeId };
}

// ============================================================================
// SHAPE ELEMENT
// ============================================================================

function buildShapeRequests(element, slideId) {
  element = validateElement(element);
  const requests = [];
  const shapeId = element.objectId || generateObjectId();
  const shapeType = SHAPE_TYPE_MAP[element.shape] || 'RECTANGLE';

  // Shadow first
  if (element.shadow) {
    requests.push(...buildFakeShadowRequests(element, slideId, shapeType));
  }

  // Create shape
  requests.push({
    createShape: {
      objectId: shapeId,
      shapeType: shapeType,
      elementProperties: {
        pageObjectId: slideId,
        size: buildSize(element.w || 100, element.h || 100),
        transform: buildTransform(element.x || 0, element.y || 0, element.rotation, element.w || 100, element.h || 100)
      }
    }
  });

  // Shape properties
  const shapeProperties = {};
  const fields = [];

  // Fill
  const originalFillColor = element._originalFillColor || element.fillColor;
  const isTransparent = originalFillColor === 'transparent' || originalFillColor === 'none';

  if (isTransparent) {
    shapeProperties.shapeBackgroundFill = { propertyState: 'NOT_RENDERED' };
    fields.push('shapeBackgroundFill');
  } else if (element.fillColor) {
    const rgb = hexToRgbApi(element.fillColor);
    if (rgb) {
      const alpha = element.fillAlpha !== undefined ? element.fillAlpha :
                    element.alpha !== undefined ? element.alpha : 1;
      shapeProperties.shapeBackgroundFill = {
        solidFill: { color: { rgbColor: rgb }, alpha: alpha }
      };
      fields.push('shapeBackgroundFill');
    }
  }

  // Border
  if (element.borderColor && element.borderColor !== 'none') {
    const borderRgb = hexToRgbApi(element.borderColor);
    if (borderRgb) {
      const borderAlpha = element.borderAlpha !== undefined ? element.borderAlpha : 1;
      const outline = {
        outlineFill: {
          solidFill: { color: { rgbColor: borderRgb }, alpha: borderAlpha }
        },
        weight: { magnitude: (element.borderWidth || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.LINE_WEIGHT) * SCALE, unit: 'PT' },
        propertyState: 'RENDERED'
      };
      if (element.borderDash || element.borderStyle) {
        outline.dashStyle = DASH_STYLE_MAP[element.borderDash || element.borderStyle] || 'SOLID';
      }
      shapeProperties.outline = outline;
      fields.push('outline');
    }
  } else {
    // Modern default: borderless
    shapeProperties.outline = { propertyState: 'NOT_RENDERED' };
    fields.push('outline');
  }

  // Vertical alignment
  if (element.verticalAlign) {
    shapeProperties.contentAlignment = VERTICAL_ALIGNMENT_MAP[element.verticalAlign] || 'MIDDLE';
    fields.push('contentAlignment');
  }

  if (fields.length > 0) {
    requests.push({
      updateShapeProperties: {
        objectId: shapeId,
        shapeProperties: shapeProperties,
        fields: fields.join(',')
      }
    });
  }

  // Text inside shape
  if (element.text) {
    requests.push({
      insertText: {
        objectId: shapeId,
        text: element.text,
        insertionIndex: 0
      }
    });

    const textStyle = {};
    const textFields = [];

    const fontSize = (element.fontSize || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.FONT_SIZE) * SCALE;
    textStyle.fontSize = { magnitude: fontSize, unit: 'PT' };
    textFields.push('fontSize');

    textStyle.fontFamily = element.fontFamily || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.FONT_FAMILY;
    textFields.push('fontFamily');

    if (element.color) {
      const textRgb = hexToRgbApi(element.color);
      if (textRgb) {
        textStyle.foregroundColor = { opaqueColor: { rgbColor: textRgb } };
        textFields.push('foregroundColor');
      }
    }

    if (element.bold) { textStyle.bold = true; textFields.push('bold'); }
    if (element.italic) { textStyle.italic = true; textFields.push('italic'); }
    if (element.underline) { textStyle.underline = true; textFields.push('underline'); }
    if (element.strikethrough) { textStyle.strikethrough = true; textFields.push('strikethrough'); }
    if (element.smallCaps) { textStyle.smallCaps = true; textFields.push('smallCaps'); }

    if (element.subscript) {
      textStyle.baselineOffset = 'SUBSCRIPT';
      textFields.push('baselineOffset');
    } else if (element.superscript) {
      textStyle.baselineOffset = 'SUPERSCRIPT';
      textFields.push('baselineOffset');
    }

    if (textFields.length > 0) {
      requests.push({
        updateTextStyle: {
          objectId: shapeId,
          style: textStyle,
          textRange: { type: 'ALL' },
          fields: textFields.join(',')
        }
      });
    }

    if (element.align) {
      requests.push({
        updateParagraphStyle: {
          objectId: shapeId,
          style: { alignment: ALIGNMENT_MAP[element.align] || 'CENTER' },
          textRange: { type: 'ALL' },
          fields: 'alignment'
        }
      });
    }
  }

  // Hyperlink
  if (element.link) {
    const linkRequest = buildLinkRequest(shapeId, element.link, 'shape');
    if (linkRequest) requests.push(linkRequest);
  }

  return { requests, objectId: shapeId };
}

// ============================================================================
// LINE ELEMENT (WITH FIXED CONNECTION TRACKING)
// ============================================================================

function buildLineRequests(element, slideId) {
  element = validateElement(element);
  const requests = [];
  const deferredConnections = [];
  const lineId = element.objectId || generateObjectId();

  // Handle elbow connectors as two straight segments
  if (element.connector === 'elbow' || element.connector === 'bent') {
    const segments = buildElbowAsSegments(element, slideId);
    return { requests: segments, deferredConnections: [], objectId: lineId };
  }

  const x1 = (element.x1 || 0) * SCALE;
  const y1 = (element.y1 || 0) * SCALE;
  const x2 = (element.x2 || 100) * SCALE;
  const y2 = (element.y2 || 100) * SCALE;

  let lineCategory = 'STRAIGHT';
  if (element.connector === 'curved') lineCategory = 'CURVED';

  const width = Math.abs(x2 - x1) || 1;
  const height = Math.abs(y2 - y1) || 1;
  const scaleX = x2 >= x1 ? 1 : -1;
  const scaleY = y2 >= y1 ? 1 : -1;

  requests.push({
    createLine: {
      objectId: lineId,
      lineCategory: lineCategory,
      elementProperties: {
        pageObjectId: slideId,
        size: {
          width: { magnitude: width, unit: 'PT' },
          height: { magnitude: height, unit: 'PT' }
        },
        transform: {
          scaleX: scaleX, scaleY: scaleY, shearX: 0, shearY: 0,
          translateX: x1, translateY: y1, unit: 'PT'
        }
      }
    }
  });

  // Line properties
  const lineProperties = {};
  const fields = [];

  if (element.color) {
    const rgb = hexToRgbApi(element.color);
    if (rgb) {
      lineProperties.lineFill = {
        solidFill: {
          color: { rgbColor: rgb },
          alpha: element.alpha !== undefined ? element.alpha : 1
        }
      };
      fields.push('lineFill');
    }
  }

  lineProperties.weight = { magnitude: (element.weight || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.LINE_WEIGHT) * SCALE, unit: 'PT' };
  fields.push('weight');

  if (element.dash) {
    lineProperties.dashStyle = DASH_STYLE_MAP[element.dash] || 'SOLID';
    fields.push('dashStyle');
  }

  if (element.startArrow && element.startArrow !== 'NONE') {
    lineProperties.startArrow = ARROW_TYPE_MAP[element.startArrow] || 'NONE';
    fields.push('startArrow');
  }

  if (element.endArrow && element.endArrow !== 'NONE') {
    lineProperties.endArrow = ARROW_TYPE_MAP[element.endArrow] || 'NONE';
    fields.push('endArrow');
  }

  if (fields.length > 0) {
    requests.push({
      updateLineProperties: {
        objectId: lineId,
        lineProperties: lineProperties,
        fields: fields.join(',')
      }
    });
  }

  // FIXED: Defer connections with proper tracking
  const hasStartConnect = element.startConnect && element.startConnect.objectId;
  const hasEndConnect = element.endConnect && element.endConnect.objectId;

  if (hasStartConnect || hasEndConnect) {
    const connectionProperties = {};
    const connectionFields = [];

    if (hasStartConnect) {
      connectionProperties.startConnection = {
        connectedObjectId: element.startConnect.objectId,
        connectionSiteIndex: element.startConnect.site || 0
      };
      connectionFields.push('startConnection');
    }

    if (hasEndConnect) {
      connectionProperties.endConnection = {
        connectedObjectId: element.endConnect.objectId,
        connectionSiteIndex: element.endConnect.site || 0
      };
      connectionFields.push('endConnection');
    }

    deferredConnections.push({
      updateLineProperties: {
        objectId: lineId,
        lineProperties: connectionProperties,
        fields: connectionFields.join(',')
      }
    });
  }

  return { requests, deferredConnections, objectId: lineId };
}

function buildElbowAsSegments(element, slideId) {
  const requests = [];
  const x1 = element.x1 || 0;
  const y1 = element.y1 || 0;
  const x2 = element.x2 || 100;
  const y2 = element.y2 || 100;
  const bendDirection = element.bendDirection || 'horizontal-first';

  let midX, midY;
  if (bendDirection === 'vertical-first') {
    midX = x1;
    midY = y2;
  } else {
    midX = x2;
    midY = y1;
  }

  const segment1 = { ...element, x1, y1, x2: midX, y2: midY, connector: null, startArrow: element.startArrow, endArrow: 'NONE' };
  const segment2 = { ...element, x1: midX, y1: midY, x2, y2, connector: null, startArrow: 'NONE', endArrow: element.endArrow };

  const seg1HasLength = (x1 !== midX || y1 !== midY);
  const seg2HasLength = (midX !== x2 || midY !== y2);

  if (seg1HasLength) requests.push(...buildStraightLineSegment(segment1, slideId));
  if (seg2HasLength) requests.push(...buildStraightLineSegment(segment2, slideId));
  if (!seg1HasLength && !seg2HasLength) requests.push(...buildStraightLineSegment(element, slideId));

  return requests;
}

function buildStraightLineSegment(element, slideId) {
  const requests = [];
  const lineId = element.objectId || generateObjectId();

  const x1 = (element.x1 || 0) * SCALE;
  const y1 = (element.y1 || 0) * SCALE;
  const x2 = (element.x2 || 100) * SCALE;
  const y2 = (element.y2 || 100) * SCALE;

  const width = Math.abs(x2 - x1) || 1;
  const height = Math.abs(y2 - y1) || 1;
  const scaleX = x2 >= x1 ? 1 : -1;
  const scaleY = y2 >= y1 ? 1 : -1;

  requests.push({
    createLine: {
      objectId: lineId,
      lineCategory: 'STRAIGHT',
      elementProperties: {
        pageObjectId: slideId,
        size: {
          width: { magnitude: width, unit: 'PT' },
          height: { magnitude: height, unit: 'PT' }
        },
        transform: {
          scaleX, scaleY, shearX: 0, shearY: 0,
          translateX: x1, translateY: y1, unit: 'PT'
        }
      }
    }
  });

  const lineProperties = {};
  const fields = [];

  if (element.color) {
    const rgb = hexToRgbApi(element.color);
    if (rgb) {
      lineProperties.lineFill = {
        solidFill: { color: { rgbColor: rgb }, alpha: element.alpha !== undefined ? element.alpha : 1 }
      };
      fields.push('lineFill');
    }
  }

  lineProperties.weight = { magnitude: (element.weight || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.LINE_WEIGHT) * SCALE, unit: 'PT' };
  fields.push('weight');

  if (element.dash) {
    lineProperties.dashStyle = DASH_STYLE_MAP[element.dash] || 'SOLID';
    fields.push('dashStyle');
  }

  if (element.startArrow && element.startArrow !== 'NONE') {
    lineProperties.startArrow = ARROW_TYPE_MAP[element.startArrow] || 'NONE';
    fields.push('startArrow');
  }

  if (element.endArrow && element.endArrow !== 'NONE') {
    lineProperties.endArrow = ARROW_TYPE_MAP[element.endArrow] || 'NONE';
    fields.push('endArrow');
  }

  if (fields.length > 0) {
    requests.push({
      updateLineProperties: {
        objectId: lineId,
        lineProperties: lineProperties,
        fields: fields.join(',')
      }
    });
  }

  return requests;
}

// ============================================================================
// OTHER ELEMENTS (IMAGE, VIDEO, TABLE, ICON)
// ============================================================================

function buildImageRequests(element, slideId) {
  element = validateElement(element);
  const requests = [];
  const imageId = element.objectId || generateObjectId();

  if (!element.url) {
    Logger.log('Image element missing URL');
    return { requests, objectId: imageId };
  }

  requests.push({
    createImage: {
      objectId: imageId,
      url: element.url,
      elementProperties: {
        pageObjectId: slideId,
        size: buildSize(element.w || 200, element.h || 150),
        transform: buildTransform(element.x || 0, element.y || 0, element.rotation, element.w || 200, element.h || 150)
      }
    }
  });

  if (element.altText || element.altTitle) {
    requests.push({
      updatePageElementAltText: {
        objectId: imageId,
        title: element.altTitle || '',
        description: element.altText || ''
      }
    });
  }

  return { requests, objectId: imageId };
}

function buildVideoRequests(element, slideId) {
  element = validateElement(element);
  const requests = [];
  const videoId = generateObjectId();

  if (!element.id || !element.source) {
    Logger.log('Video element missing id or source');
    return { requests, objectId: videoId };
  }

  const source = element.source.toUpperCase() === 'YOUTUBE' ? 'YOUTUBE' : 'DRIVE';

  requests.push({
    createVideo: {
      objectId: videoId,
      source: source,
      id: element.id,
      elementProperties: {
        pageObjectId: slideId,
        size: buildSize(element.w || 400, element.h || 225),
        transform: buildTransform(element.x || 0, element.y || 0, element.rotation, element.w || 400, element.h || 225)
      }
    }
  });

  return { requests, objectId: videoId };
}

function buildTableRequests(element, slideId) {
  element = validateElement(element);
  const requests = [];
  const tableId = element.objectId || generateObjectId();

  if (!element.data || !Array.isArray(element.data) || element.data.length === 0) {
    Logger.log('Table element missing data');
    return { requests, objectId: tableId };
  }

  const rows = element.data.length;
  const cols = element.data[0].length || 1;
  const bounds = transformCoordinates(element.x || 0, element.y || 0, element.w || 400, element.h || 200);

  requests.push({
    createTable: {
      objectId: tableId,
      rows: rows,
      columns: cols,
      elementProperties: {
        pageObjectId: slideId,
        size: {
          width: { magnitude: bounds.w, unit: 'PT' },
          height: { magnitude: bounds.h, unit: 'PT' }
        },
        transform: {
          scaleX: 1, scaleY: 1,
          translateX: bounds.x, translateY: bounds.y, unit: 'PT'
        }
      }
    }
  });

  const tableFontSize = (element.fontSize || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.TABLE_FONT_SIZE) * SCALE;

  for (let r = 0; r < rows; r++) {
    for (let c = 0; c < cols; c++) {
      const value = element.data[r][c];
      if (value !== null && value !== undefined && value !== '') {
        requests.push({
          insertText: {
            objectId: tableId,
            cellLocation: { rowIndex: r, columnIndex: c },
            text: String(value),
            insertionIndex: 0
          }
        });

        const isHeader = r === 0 && element.headerRow !== false;
        const textStyle = {
          fontSize: { magnitude: tableFontSize, unit: 'PT' },
          fontFamily: element.fontFamily || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.FONT_FAMILY
        };
        const fields = ['fontSize', 'fontFamily'];

        if (isHeader) {
          textStyle.bold = true;
          fields.push('bold');
        }

        requests.push({
          updateTextStyle: {
            objectId: tableId,
            cellLocation: { rowIndex: r, columnIndex: c },
            style: textStyle,
            textRange: { type: 'ALL' },
            fields: fields.join(',')
          }
        });

        if (isHeader) {
          requests.push({
            updateTableCellProperties: {
              objectId: tableId,
              tableRange: {
                location: { rowIndex: r, columnIndex: c },
                rowSpan: 1, columnSpan: 1
              },
              tableCellProperties: {
                tableCellBackgroundFill: {
                  solidFill: {
                    color: { rgbColor: hexToRgbApi(CONFIG.DEFAULTS.TABLE_HEADER_BG) },
                    alpha: 1
                  }
                }
              },
              fields: 'tableCellBackgroundFill'
            }
          });
        }
      }
    }
  }

  if (element.merges && Array.isArray(element.merges)) {
    element.merges.forEach(merge => {
      requests.push({
        mergeTableCells: {
          objectId: tableId,
          tableRange: {
            location: { rowIndex: merge.startRow, columnIndex: merge.startCol },
            rowSpan: merge.endRow - merge.startRow + 1,
            columnSpan: merge.endCol - merge.startCol + 1
          }
        }
      });
    });
  }

  return { requests, objectId: tableId };
}

function buildIconRequests(element, slideId) {
  element = validateElement(element);
  const requests = [];
  const size = element.size || 48;
  const x = element.x || 0;
  const y = element.y || 0;

  const iconSymbols = {
    'chart-line': '\u2197', 'chart-bar': '\u2581', 'users': '\u263A',
    'dollar': '$', 'trending-up': '\u2191', 'star': '\u2605',
    'check': '\u2713', 'x': '\u2717', 'alert': '\u26A0',
    'info': '\u2139', 'rocket': '\u2708', 'target': '\u25CE',
    'zap': '\u26A1', 'shield': '\u26E8', 'lock': '\u26BF',
    'globe': '\u2295', 'clock': '\u23F0', 'calendar': '\u26AA',
    'mail': '\u2709', 'phone': '\u260E', 'download': '\u21E9',
    'upload': '\u21E7', 'search': '\u26B2', 'settings': '\u2699',
    'heart': '\u2665', 'briefcase': '\u26AB'
  };

  const symbol = iconSymbols[element.icon] || '\u25CF';

  const circleId = generateObjectId();
  requests.push({
    createShape: {
      objectId: circleId,
      shapeType: 'ELLIPSE',
      elementProperties: {
        pageObjectId: slideId,
        size: buildSize(size, size),
        transform: buildTransform(x, y, element.rotation, size, size)
      }
    }
  });

  const iconColor = resolveThemeColor(element.color) || CONFIG.DEFAULTS.ICON_COLOR;
  const rgb = hexToRgbApi(iconColor);
  const bgOpacity = element.bgOpacity !== undefined ? element.bgOpacity : CONFIG.DEFAULTS.ICON_BG_OPACITY;

  requests.push({
    updateShapeProperties: {
      objectId: circleId,
      shapeProperties: {
        shapeBackgroundFill: {
          solidFill: { color: { rgbColor: rgb }, alpha: bgOpacity }
        },
        outline: { propertyState: 'NOT_RENDERED' }
      },
      fields: 'shapeBackgroundFill,outline'
    }
  });

  const textId = generateObjectId();
  requests.push({
    createShape: {
      objectId: textId,
      shapeType: 'TEXT_BOX',
      elementProperties: {
        pageObjectId: slideId,
        size: buildSize(size, size),
        transform: buildTransform(x, y, element.rotation, size, size)
      }
    }
  });

  requests.push({
    insertText: {
      objectId: textId,
      text: symbol,
      insertionIndex: 0
    }
  });

  requests.push({
    updateTextStyle: {
      objectId: textId,
      style: {
        fontSize: { magnitude: size * 0.5 * SCALE, unit: 'PT' },
        foregroundColor: { opaqueColor: { rgbColor: rgb } }
      },
      textRange: { type: 'ALL' },
      fields: 'fontSize,foregroundColor'
    }
  });

  requests.push({
    updateParagraphStyle: {
      objectId: textId,
      style: { alignment: 'CENTER' },
      textRange: { type: 'ALL' },
      fields: 'alignment'
    }
  });

  return { requests, objectId: circleId };
}

// ============================================================================
// MAIN REQUEST BUILDER (WITH FIXED TRACKING)
// ============================================================================

/**
 * Build requests for element - NOW WITH PROPER ID TRACKING
 */
function buildElementRequests(element, slideId, slideIndex, elementIndex) {
  try {
    let result = { requests: [], objectId: null, deferredConnections: [] };

    switch (element.type) {
      case 'text':
        result = buildTextRequests(element, slideId);
        break;
      case 'shape':
        result = buildShapeRequests(element, slideId);
        break;
      case 'line':
        result = buildLineRequests(element, slideId);
        break;
      case 'image':
        result = buildImageRequests(element, slideId);
        break;
      case 'video':
        result = buildVideoRequests(element, slideId);
        break;
      case 'table':
        result = buildTableRequests(element, slideId);
        break;
      case 'icon':
        result = buildIconRequests(element, slideId);
        break;
      case 'chart':
        // Charts handled in Phase 2
        phase2Queue.charts.push({ slideIndex, chartSpec: element });
        Logger.log(`Chart queued for Phase 2: slide ${slideIndex}`);
        break;
      default:
        Logger.log('Unknown element type: ' + element.type);
    }

    // FIXED: Record objectId for Phase 2 lookups (grouping, connections)
    if (result.objectId) {
      phase2Queue.recordElementId(slideIndex, elementIndex, result.objectId);
      // Store on element too for inline references
      element._objectId = result.objectId;
    }

    return result;
  } catch (e) {
    Logger.log('Error building element requests: ' + e.message);
    return { requests: [], objectId: null, deferredConnections: [] };
  }
}

/**
 * Build all requests for entire presentation
 */
function buildAllRequests(json, firstSlideId) {
  const requests = [];
  const slideIds = [];
  const deferredConnections = [];

  json.slides.forEach((slide, slideIndex) => {
    slide = normalizeProperties(slide);

    let slideId;
    const hasCustomElements = slide.elements && slide.elements.length > 0;
    const layoutKey = hasCustomElements ? 'blank' : (slide.layout || 'blank');

    if (slideIndex === 0) {
      slideId = firstSlideId;
    } else {
      slideId = generateObjectId();
      requests.push({
        createSlide: {
          objectId: slideId,
          insertionIndex: slideIndex,
          slideLayoutReference: { predefinedLayout: 'BLANK' }
        }
      });
    }
    slideIds.push(slideId);

    // Background
    if (slide.backgroundImage) {
      requests.push({
        updatePageProperties: {
          objectId: slideId,
          pageProperties: {
            pageBackgroundFill: {
              stretchedPictureFill: { contentUrl: slide.backgroundImage }
            }
          },
          fields: 'pageBackgroundFill.stretchedPictureFill'
        }
      });
    } else if (slide.background) {
      const bgColor = normalizeColor(resolveThemeColor(slide.background));
      const rgb = hexToRgbApi(bgColor);
      if (rgb) {
        requests.push({
          updatePageProperties: {
            objectId: slideId,
            pageProperties: {
              pageBackgroundFill: {
                solidFill: { color: { rgbColor: rgb } }
              }
            },
            fields: 'pageBackgroundFill.solidFill.color'
          }
        });
      }
    }

    // Sort elements by zIndex
    let elements = slide.elements || [];
    elements = elements.map((el, idx) => ({
      ...el,
      _originalIndex: idx,
      zIndex: el.zIndex !== undefined ? el.zIndex : idx
    }));
    elements.sort((a, b) => a.zIndex - b.zIndex);

    // Build requests for each element - NOW PASSING elementIndex
    elements.forEach((element, elementIndex) => {
      const result = buildElementRequests(element, slideId, slideIndex, element._originalIndex);
      requests.push(...result.requests);
      if (result.deferredConnections && result.deferredConnections.length > 0) {
        deferredConnections.push(...result.deferredConnections);
      }
    });

    // Queue speaker notes for Phase 2
    const notesText = slide.speakerNotes || slide.notes;
    if (notesText) {
      phase2Queue.speakerNotes.push({ slideIndex, notes: notesText });
    }

    // Queue groups for Phase 2 (if using elementIndices)
    if (slide.groups && Array.isArray(slide.groups)) {
      slide.groups.forEach(group => {
        // Convert element indices to actual objectIds
        if (group.elementIndices) {
          const elementIds = group.elementIndices.map(idx => 
            phase2Queue.getElementId(slideIndex, idx)
          ).filter(id => id); // Remove nulls

          if (elementIds.length >= 2) {
            phase2Queue.groups.push({ slideIndex, elementIds });
          }
        } else if (group.elementIds) {
          // Already has IDs
          phase2Queue.groups.push({ slideIndex, elementIds: group.elementIds });
        }
      });
    }
  });

  // Append deferred connections
  if (deferredConnections.length > 0) {
    Logger.log(`Appending ${deferredConnections.length} deferred line connection(s)`);
    requests.push(...deferredConnections);
  }

  return { requests, slideIds };
}

// ============================================================================
// PHASE 2: SLIDESAPP (FIXED IMPLEMENTATIONS)
// ============================================================================

/**
 * Execute Phase 2 operations - DIAGNOSTIC VERSION WITH DETAILED LOGGING
 */
function executePhase2(presentation, json, slideIds) {
  if (!CONFIG.PHASE2.ENABLED) {
    Logger.log('Phase 2 disabled');
    return { success: true, operations: [], errors: [] };
  }

  Logger.log('=== PHASE 2 DIAGNOSTIC MODE ACTIVE ===');
  
  const results = {
    success: true,
    operations: [],
    errors: []
  };

  const slides = presentation.getSlides();
  Logger.log(`📊 Presentation has ${slides.length} slide(s)`);
  Logger.log(`📋 Phase 2 Queue Status:
  - Charts: ${phase2Queue.charts.length}
  - Speaker Notes: ${phase2Queue.speakerNotes.length}
  - Groups: ${phase2Queue.groups.length}`);

  // 1. Remove layout placeholders from slides with custom elements
  Logger.log('Phase 2: Removing placeholders');
  json.slides.forEach((slideSpec, index) => {
    if (index >= slides.length) return;
    if (!slideSpec.elements || slideSpec.elements.length === 0) return;

    const slide = slides[index];
    try {
      const pageElements = slide.getPageElements();
      const elementsToRemove = [];

      pageElements.forEach(element => {
        try {
          const shape = element.asShape();
          if (shape) {
            let shouldRemove = false;

            try {
              const placeholderType = shape.getPlaceholderType();
              if (placeholderType !== SlidesApp.PlaceholderType.NONE) {
                shouldRemove = true;
              }
            } catch (e) {}

            if (!shouldRemove) {
              try {
                const textRange = shape.getText();
                if (textRange) {
                  const text = textRange.asString();
                  if (text && (
                    text.includes('Click to add') ||
                    text.includes('click to add') ||
                    text.trim().match(/^(XX%|##|X+%?)$/)
                  )) {
                    shouldRemove = true;
                  }
                }
              } catch (e) {}
            }

            if (shouldRemove) {
              elementsToRemove.push(element);
            }
          }
        } catch (e) {}
      });

      elementsToRemove.forEach(element => {
        try {
          element.remove();
        } catch (e) {
          Logger.log(`Phase 2: Failed to remove element: ${e.message}`);
        }
      });

      if (elementsToRemove.length > 0) {
        results.operations.push({ type: 'removePlaceholders', slide: index, count: elementsToRemove.length, success: true });
      }
    } catch (e) {
      results.errors.push({ type: 'removePlaceholders', slide: index, error: e.message });
    }
  });

  // 2. DIAGNOSTIC: Create charts with detailed logging
  if (CONFIG.PHASE2.CHARTS && phase2Queue.charts.length > 0) {
    Logger.log(`\n🎨 === CHART CREATION (${phase2Queue.charts.length} chart(s)) ===`);
    phase2Queue.charts.forEach((chartItem, idx) => {
      Logger.log(`\n📈 Chart ${idx + 1}/${phase2Queue.charts.length}:`);
      Logger.log(`  Slide: ${chartItem.slideIndex}`);
      Logger.log(`  Type: ${chartItem.chartSpec.chartType}`);
      Logger.log(`  Data rows: ${chartItem.chartSpec.data ? chartItem.chartSpec.data.length : 0}`);
      Logger.log(`  Position: (${chartItem.chartSpec.x}, ${chartItem.chartSpec.y})`);
      Logger.log(`  Size: ${chartItem.chartSpec.w}x${chartItem.chartSpec.h}`);
      
      if (chartItem.slideIndex >= slides.length) {
        Logger.log(`  ❌ ERROR: Invalid slide index ${chartItem.slideIndex} (max ${slides.length - 1})`);
        results.errors.push({ type: 'chart', slide: chartItem.slideIndex, error: 'Invalid slide index' });
        return;
      }

      const targetSlide = slides[chartItem.slideIndex];
      try {
        Logger.log(`  ⏳ Creating chart...`);
        createChartPhase2Diagnostic(targetSlide, chartItem.chartSpec, idx + 1);
        Logger.log(`  ✅ Chart created successfully`);
        results.operations.push({ type: 'chart', slide: chartItem.slideIndex, success: true });
      } catch (e) {
        Logger.log(`  ❌ CHART FAILED: ${e.message}`);
        Logger.log(`  Stack: ${e.stack || 'No stack trace'}`);
        results.errors.push({ type: 'chart', slide: chartItem.slideIndex, error: e.message });
      }
    });
  }

  // 3. DIAGNOSTIC: Speaker notes with detailed logging
  if (CONFIG.PHASE2.SPEAKER_NOTES && phase2Queue.speakerNotes.length > 0) {
    Logger.log(`\n📝 === SPEAKER NOTES (${phase2Queue.speakerNotes.length} note(s)) ===`);
    phase2Queue.speakerNotes.forEach((noteItem, idx) => {
      Logger.log(`\n📄 Note ${idx + 1}/${phase2Queue.speakerNotes.length}:`);
      Logger.log(`  Slide: ${noteItem.slideIndex}`);
      Logger.log(`  Length: ${noteItem.notes.length} chars`);
      Logger.log(`  Preview: "${noteItem.notes.substring(0, 50)}${noteItem.notes.length > 50 ? '...' : ''}"`);
      
      if (noteItem.slideIndex >= slides.length) {
        Logger.log(`  ❌ ERROR: Invalid slide index ${noteItem.slideIndex} (max ${slides.length - 1})`);
        results.errors.push({ type: 'speakerNotes', slide: noteItem.slideIndex, error: 'Invalid slide index' });
        return;
      }

      const slide = slides[noteItem.slideIndex];
      try {
        Logger.log(`  ⏳ Adding speaker notes...`);
        addSpeakerNotesDiagnostic(slide, noteItem.notes, noteItem.slideIndex);
        Logger.log(`  ✅ Notes added successfully`);
        results.operations.push({ type: 'speakerNotes', slide: noteItem.slideIndex, success: true });
      } catch (e) {
        Logger.log(`  ❌ NOTES FAILED: ${e.message}`);
        Logger.log(`  Stack: ${e.stack || 'No stack trace'}`);
        results.errors.push({ type: 'speakerNotes', slide: noteItem.slideIndex, error: e.message });
      }
    });
  }

  // 4. DIAGNOSTIC: Groups with detailed element lookup logging
  if (CONFIG.PHASE2.GROUPS && phase2Queue.groups.length > 0) {
    Logger.log(`\n🔗 === GROUPS (${phase2Queue.groups.length} group(s)) ===`);
    phase2Queue.groups.forEach((groupItem, idx) => {
      Logger.log(`\n👥 Group ${idx + 1}/${phase2Queue.groups.length}:`);
      Logger.log(`  Slide: ${groupItem.slideIndex}`);
      Logger.log(`  Target elements: ${groupItem.elementIds.length}`);
      Logger.log(`  Element IDs: ${JSON.stringify(groupItem.elementIds)}`);
      
      if (groupItem.slideIndex >= slides.length) {
        Logger.log(`  ❌ ERROR: Invalid slide index ${groupItem.slideIndex} (max ${slides.length - 1})`);
        results.errors.push({ type: 'group', slide: groupItem.slideIndex, error: 'Invalid slide index' });
        return;
      }

      const slide = slides[groupItem.slideIndex];
      try {
        Logger.log(`  ⏳ Creating group...`);
        createGroupDiagnostic(slide, groupItem.elementIds, groupItem.slideIndex);
        Logger.log(`  ✅ Group created successfully`);
        results.operations.push({ type: 'group', slide: groupItem.slideIndex, success: true });
      } catch (e) {
        Logger.log(`  ❌ GROUP FAILED: ${e.message}`);
        Logger.log(`  Stack: ${e.stack || 'No stack trace'}`);
        results.errors.push({ type: 'group', slide: groupItem.slideIndex, error: e.message });
      }
    });
  }

  // Summary
  Logger.log(`\n📊 === PHASE 2 SUMMARY ===`);
  Logger.log(`✅ Successful operations: ${results.operations.length}`);
  Logger.log(`❌ Failed operations: ${results.errors.length}`);
  if (results.errors.length > 0) {
    Logger.log(`\n⚠️ Error breakdown:`);
    results.errors.forEach((err, i) => {
      Logger.log(`  ${i + 1}. ${err.type} on slide ${err.slide}: ${err.error}`);
    });
  }

  results.success = results.errors.length === 0;
  return results;
}

/**
 * DIAGNOSTIC: Chart creation with step-by-step logging
 */
function createChartPhase2Diagnostic(slide, chartSpec, chartNum) {
  Logger.log(`    Step 1: Validating chart data...`);
  if (!chartSpec.data || !Array.isArray(chartSpec.data) || chartSpec.data.length < 2) {
    throw new Error('Chart requires at least header row + 1 data row');
  }
  Logger.log(`    ✓ Data valid: ${chartSpec.data.length} rows`);

  // Create spreadsheet
  Logger.log(`    Step 2: Creating temporary spreadsheet...`);
  let spreadsheet, sheet, spreadsheetId;
  try {
    spreadsheet = SpreadsheetApp.create('SlidesEngine_Chart_' + chartNum + '_' + Date.now());
    sheet = spreadsheet.getActiveSheet();
    spreadsheetId = spreadsheet.getId();
    Logger.log(`    ✓ Spreadsheet created: ${spreadsheetId}`);
  } catch (e) {
    throw new Error(`Failed to create spreadsheet: ${e.message}`);
  }

  // Write data
  Logger.log(`    Step 3: Writing chart data to spreadsheet...`);
  try {
    const rows = chartSpec.data.length;
    const cols = chartSpec.data[0].length;
    Logger.log(`      Writing ${rows}x${cols} data range...`);
    sheet.getRange(1, 1, rows, cols).setValues(chartSpec.data);
    SpreadsheetApp.flush();
    Logger.log(`    ✓ Data written and flushed`);
  } catch (e) {
    throw new Error(`Failed to write data: ${e.message}`);
  }

  // Build chart
  Logger.log(`    Step 4: Building chart in spreadsheet...`);
  const chartTypeMap = {
    'BAR': Charts.ChartType.BAR,
    'LINE': Charts.ChartType.LINE,
    'AREA': Charts.ChartType.AREA,
    'PIE': Charts.ChartType.PIE,
    'COLUMN': Charts.ChartType.COLUMN,
    'SCATTER': Charts.ChartType.SCATTER
  };
  const chartType = chartTypeMap[(chartSpec.chartType || 'COLUMN').toUpperCase()] || Charts.ChartType.COLUMN;
  Logger.log(`      Chart type: ${chartSpec.chartType || 'COLUMN'}`);

  try {
    const chartBuilder = sheet.newChart()
      .setChartType(chartType)
      .addRange(sheet.getDataRange())
      .setPosition(1, chartSpec.data[0].length + 2, 0, 0);

    if (chartSpec.title) {
      chartBuilder.setOption('title', chartSpec.title);
      Logger.log(`      Title: "${chartSpec.title}"`);
    }

    const chart = chartBuilder.build();
    sheet.insertChart(chart);
    SpreadsheetApp.flush();
    Logger.log(`    ✓ Chart built in spreadsheet`);
  } catch (e) {
    throw new Error(`Failed to build chart: ${e.message}`);
  }

  Logger.log(`    Step 5: Retrieving chart from spreadsheet...`);
  const charts = sheet.getCharts();
  if (charts.length === 0) {
    throw new Error('Chart was not created in spreadsheet');
  }
  const sourceChart = charts[0];
  Logger.log(`    ✓ Chart retrieved (${charts.length} chart(s) in sheet)`);

  // Calculate position
  const x = (chartSpec.x || 0) * SCALE;
  const y = (chartSpec.y || 0) * SCALE;
  const w = (chartSpec.w || 400) * SCALE;
  const h = (chartSpec.h || 300) * SCALE;
  Logger.log(`    Step 6: Inserting into slide...`);
  Logger.log(`      Position: (${x.toFixed(1)}, ${y.toFixed(1)})`);
  Logger.log(`      Size: ${w.toFixed(1)}x${h.toFixed(1)}`);

  // SINGLE RELIABLE METHOD: Insert then position
  try {
    Logger.log(`      Attempting insertSheetsChart()...`);
    const insertedChart = slide.insertSheetsChart(sourceChart);
    insertedChart.setLeft(x);
    insertedChart.setTop(y);
    insertedChart.setWidth(w);
    insertedChart.setHeight(h);
    Logger.log(`    ✓ Chart inserted successfully (linked)`);
    return { spreadsheetId };
  } catch (e) {
    Logger.log(`      ⚠️ insertSheetsChart failed: ${e.message}`);
    // Fallback: Try as image if linked chart fails
    try {
      Logger.log(`      Attempting insertSheetsChartAsImage() fallback...`);
      const insertedChart = slide.insertSheetsChartAsImage(sourceChart);
      insertedChart.setLeft(x);
      insertedChart.setTop(y);
      insertedChart.setWidth(w);
      insertedChart.setHeight(h);
      Logger.log(`    ✓ Chart inserted as image (fallback)`);
      return { spreadsheetId };
    } catch (e2) {
      throw new Error('Chart insertion failed: ' + e.message + ' | Fallback: ' + e2.message);
    }
  }
}

/**
 * DIAGNOSTIC: Group creation with detailed element lookup logging
 */
function createGroupDiagnostic(slide, elementIds, slideIndex) {
  Logger.log(`    Step 1: Validating input...`);
  if (!elementIds || elementIds.length < 2) {
    throw new Error('Need at least 2 elements to create a group');
  }
  Logger.log(`    ✓ Need to group ${elementIds.length} elements`);

  Logger.log(`    Step 2: Getting all page elements from slide ${slideIndex}...`);
  const pageElements = slide.getPageElements();
  Logger.log(`    ✓ Found ${pageElements.length} total elements on slide`);

  Logger.log(`    Step 3: Looking up each target element...`);
  const elementsToGroup = [];
  const foundIds = [];
  const notFoundIds = [];

  elementIds.forEach((targetId, idx) => {
    Logger.log(`      Looking for element ${idx + 1}/${elementIds.length}: "${targetId}"`);
    let found = false;
    
    for (let i = 0; i < pageElements.length; i++) {
      const elementId = pageElements[i].getObjectId();
      if (elementId === targetId) {
        elementsToGroup.push(pageElements[i]);
        foundIds.push(targetId);
        Logger.log(`        ✓ Found at page element index ${i}`);
        found = true;
        break;
      }
    }
    
    if (!found) {
      notFoundIds.push(targetId);
      Logger.log(`        ❌ NOT FOUND`);
    }
  });

  Logger.log(`    Step 4: Element lookup results:`);
  Logger.log(`      Found: ${foundIds.length}/${elementIds.length}`);
  if (foundIds.length > 0) {
    Logger.log(`      Found IDs: ${JSON.stringify(foundIds)}`);
  }
  if (notFoundIds.length > 0) {
    Logger.log(`      ⚠️ Missing IDs: ${JSON.stringify(notFoundIds)}`);
  }

  if (elementsToGroup.length < 2) {
    // List all available IDs for debugging
    Logger.log(`    Available element IDs on slide:`);
    pageElements.forEach((el, i) => {
      Logger.log(`      ${i}: ${el.getObjectId()}`);
    });
    throw new Error(`Only found ${elementsToGroup.length} of ${elementIds.length} elements for grouping`);
  }

  Logger.log(`    Step 5: Grouping ${elementsToGroup.length} elements...`);
  try {
    slide.group(elementsToGroup);
    Logger.log(`    ✓ Group created successfully`);
  } catch (e) {
    throw new Error(`Failed to create group: ${e.message}`);
  }
}

// ============================================================================
// MAIN GENERATION FUNCTION
// ============================================================================

/**
 * Generate presentation - PRODUCTION READY
 */
function generatePresentation(json) {
  // Reset Phase 2 queue
  phase2Queue.reset();

  // Validate Advanced Service
  if (typeof Slides === 'undefined') {
    throw new Error('Advanced Slides API not enabled. Enable in Services menu.');
  }

  // Validate JSON
  json = validateJSON(json);

  // Initialize theme
  setTheme(json.config && json.config.theme);

  // Create presentation
  const title = (json.config && json.config.title) || 'Untitled Presentation';
  const presentation = SlidesApp.create(title);
  const presentationId = presentation.getId();

  Logger.log(`=== PHASE 1: Slides API batchUpdate ===`);
  Logger.log(`Created presentation: ${title} (${presentationId})`);

  // Get first slide and delete placeholders
  const firstSlide = presentation.getSlides()[0];
  const firstSlideId = firstSlide.getObjectId();

  const placeholderElements = firstSlide.getPageElements();
  const deleteRequests = [];

  placeholderElements.forEach(element => {
    try {
      const objectId = element.getObjectId();
      if (objectId) {
        deleteRequests.push({ deleteObject: { objectId } });
      }
    } catch (e) {}
  });

  Logger.log(`Deleting ${deleteRequests.length} placeholder elements`);

  // Build content requests
  const { requests: contentRequests, slideIds } = buildAllRequests(json, firstSlideId);

  // Combine delete + content
  const allRequests = [...deleteRequests, ...contentRequests];

  Logger.log(`Built ${allRequests.length} total requests (${deleteRequests.length} deletes + ${contentRequests.length} content)`);

  // Execute Phase 1
  if (allRequests.length > 0) {
    try {
      const response = Slides.Presentations.batchUpdate({
        requests: allRequests
      }, presentationId);

      Logger.log(`Phase 1 successful: ${response.replies.length} replies`);
    } catch (e) {
      Logger.log('Phase 1 error: ' + e.message);
      try {
        DriveApp.getFileById(presentationId).setTrashed(true);
      } catch (cleanupError) {}
      throw new Error('Failed to create presentation: ' + e.message);
    }
  }

  // Execute Phase 2
  Logger.log('=== PHASE 2: SlidesApp features ===');
  let phase2Results = { success: true, operations: [], errors: [] };

  try {
    const updatedPresentation = SlidesApp.openById(presentationId);
    phase2Results = executePhase2(updatedPresentation, json, slideIds);

    if (phase2Results.operations.length > 0) {
      Logger.log(`Phase 2 completed: ${phase2Results.operations.length} operations`);
    }
    if (phase2Results.errors.length > 0) {
      Logger.log(`Phase 2 had ${phase2Results.errors.length} non-fatal errors`);
    }
  } catch (e) {
    Logger.log('Phase 2 error (non-fatal): ' + e.message);
    phase2Results.errors.push({ type: 'phase2', error: e.message });
  }

  // Return results
  const refreshedPresentation = SlidesApp.openById(presentationId);
  const url = refreshedPresentation.getUrl();
  const slideCount = refreshedPresentation.getSlides().length;

  Logger.log(`Presentation complete: ${url}`);

  return {
    id: presentationId,
    url: url,
    slideCount: slideCount,
    title: title,
    phase2: {
      success: phase2Results.success,
      operations: phase2Results.operations.length,
      warnings: phase2Results.errors.length,
      // Surface warnings for UI display
      warningDetails: phase2Results.errors.length > 0 ? 
        phase2Results.errors.map(e => `${e.type}: ${e.error}`).join('; ') : null
    }
  };
}

      codename: CONFIG.CODENAME,

    }, null, 2)).setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);

function doPost(e) {
  try {
    const json = JSON.parse(e.postData.contents);
    const result = generatePresentation(json);

    return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify({
      success: true,
      presentationId: result.id,
      url: result.url,
      slideCount: result.slideCount,
      phase2Warnings: result.phase2.warningDetails,
      version: CONFIG.VERSION,
      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()

  } catch (err) {
    return ContentService.createTextOutput(JSON.stringify({
      success: false,
      error: err.message,
      version: CONFIG.VERSION,
      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
    }, null, 2)).setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
  }

# Developer Brief: JSON-to-Slides Automation (Hybrid Engine)

## 1. Project Overview

The goal is to generate complex Google Slides presentations automatically from a JSON data source.
**Current Status:** We are transitioning from a pure `SlidesApp` (slow but stable) approach to a Hybrid approach using the **Google Slides API** (fast) for structure and **SlidesApp** (native) for special features.

## 2. The Core Technical Challenge

**The Synchronization Issue ("The Ghost Slide Problem")**
When we use the Advanced Slides API (`Slides.Presentations.batchUpdate`) to create slides, the changes occur on Google's servers instantly. However, the executing Apps Script instance, if already running `SlidesApp`, operates on a cached version of the deck.

* **Symptoms:** The script creates slides successfully, but when it tries to add Charts or Speaker Notes immediately after, it throws errors (e.g., "Slide not found" or "Index out of bounds") because `SlidesApp` does not yet "see" the slides created by the API.
* **Solution:** A **Two-Phase Execution Model** with a forced re-fetch of the presentation.

---

## 3. Required Architecture: The Two-Phase Model

The script must run sequentially in a single execution without user intervention.

### Phase 1: The "Heavy Lifting" (API)

* **Tool:** `Slides.Presentations.batchUpdate`
* **Task:** Create the slides, set backgrounds, add text boxes, add shapes, insert static images.
* **Why:** It is significantly faster and allows for batching hundreds of requests.

### The Bridge: Synchronization

* **Task:** Force the script to wait for server propagation and then reload the file.
* **Implementation:**
```javascript
// 1. Send the API batch
Slides.Presentations.batchUpdate({'requests': requests}, deckId);

// 2. WAIT. Allow Google servers to process the changes.
Utilities.sleep(2000); // 2 seconds

// 3. RE-OPEN. Use SlidesApp to open the deck by ID.
// This forces a fresh fetch of the document state.
var freshDeck = SlidesApp.openById(deckId);

```



### Phase 2: The "Native Features" (SlidesApp)

* **Tool:** `SlidesApp` methods on the `freshDeck` object.
* **Task:** Insert Google Sheets Charts (linked) and add Speaker Notes.
* **Why:** The API currently does not support creating linked Charts or easily modifying Speaker Notes text without complex shape-lookup logic.

---

## 4. Implementation Details & Snippets

### A. JSON Structure Requirements

The JSON input must support these keys at the slide level:

```json
{
  "slides": [
    {
      "id": "slide_001",
      "title": "Monthly Performance",
      "speakerNotes": "Emphasis on Q3 growth...",
      "charts": [
        {
          "spreadsheetId": "1AbC-123...",
          "chartId": "123456789", 
          "x": 50, "y": 100, "w": 400, "h": 300
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

```

### B. Feature: Adding Speaker Notes (Phase 2)

*Logic retrieved from "Project Ares" session.*
The script must access the `NotesPage` of the slide and find the specific shape reserved for the placeholder text.

```javascript
function addSpeakerNotes(slide, text) {
  if (!text) return;
  
  var notesPage = slide.getNotesPage();
  // The specific shape for notes is standard on all Google Slides
  var speakerNotesShape = notesPage.getSpeakerNotesShape();
  
  if (speakerNotesShape) {
    speakerNotesShape.getText().setText(text);
  }
}

```

### C. Feature: Embedding Linked Charts (Phase 2)

*Logic retrieved from "Stable Pro Deck" session.*
The script must search the source spreadsheet for the specific Chart ID. Indices (e.g., `charts[0]`) are unreliable if the user moves tabs or adds charts.

```javascript
function addLinkedChart(slide, chartData) {
  var ss = SpreadsheetApp.openById(chartData.spreadsheetId);
  var allSheets = ss.getSheets();
  var sourceChart = null;

  // Search loop: Find chart by unique ID
  for (var i = 0; i < allSheets.length; i++) {
    var charts = allSheets[i].getCharts();
    for (var j = 0; j < charts.length; j++) {
      if (charts[j].getChartId().toString() === chartData.chartId.toString()) {
        sourceChart = charts[j];
        break;
      }
    }
    if (sourceChart) break;
  }

  if (sourceChart) {
    // insertChart() maintains the link to live data
    var slideChart = slide.insertChart(sourceChart);
    
    // Layout
    slideChart.setLeft(chartData.x || 50);
    slideChart.setTop(chartData.y || 50);
    if (chartData.w) slideChart.setWidth(chartData.w);
    if (chartData.h) slideChart.setHeight(chartData.h);
  }
}

```

---

## 5. Execution Flow Summary

1. **Initialize:** Create empty deck using `SlidesApp.create()`. Get `deckId`.
2. **Phase 1 (API):** Parse JSON. Build `requests` array for creating slides, titles, and shapes. Execute `batchUpdate`.
3. **Sync:** `Utilities.sleep(2000)`.
4. **Phase 2 (Native):**
* Call `var deck = SlidesApp.openById(deckId)`.
* Loop through the slides: `var slides = deck.getSlides()`.
* Match JSON data to slides by index.
* Call `addSpeakerNotes()` if note data exists.
* Call `addLinkedChart()` if chart data exists.


5. **Finalize:** `deck.saveAndClose()`.

## 6. Known Pitfalls

* **Do not** attempt to mix `slide.insertShape` (Native) and `requests.push` (API) in the same loop without the Save/Reopen pattern.
* **Do not** rely on Chart Index (e.g., the 1st chart on the tab). Always match by `chartId`.
* **Do not** forget to enable the "Google Slides API" in the Apps Script "Services" menu, or the `Slides.Presentations` namespace will be undefined.

### Planner Response

Is it sufficient to deploy with "test deployment" each time?

**Yes, absolutely.**

Since you are pushing code changes frequently (`clasp push`), using the **Test Deployment** (the `/dev` URL) is the correct and most efficient workflow.

### Why?
*   **Clasp pushes to HEAD**: When you run `clasp push`, you are updating the "current state" of the project (the code visible in the editor).
*   **Test Deployment tracks HEAD**: The "Test Deployment" always runs whatever code is currently in the editor. It updates instantly when you push.
*   **No Versioning Needed**: You do **not** need to create a new "Managed Deployment" (Version 1, Version 2, etc.) for every change. That is only necessary when you want to "freeze" a stable version for other users while you continue working on new features.

**Workflow:**
1.  `clasp push`
2.  Refresh your **Test Deployment** URL.
3.  Verify.

You only need a **Managed Deployment** when you are ready to "release" a stable version to other people so that your future edits don't accidentally break their app.

### Planner Response

Great question! Let me explain the scaling system and how we can fix it.

## The Scaling System Explained

Your JSON uses a **virtual canvas** of 1000×562.5 (a nice round 16:9 ratio), but Google Slides uses **720×405 points** internally.

```javascript
// Config.gs
CANVAS: { WIDTH: 1000, HEIGHT: 562.5 }  // Your JSON coordinate system
SLIDES: { WIDTH: 720, HEIGHT: 405 }      // Google Slides actual size

const SCALE = 720 / 1000 = 0.72
```

**What happens during Generation:**
- You specify `fontSize: 32` in JSON
- Generator multiplies: `32 × 0.72 = 23.04pt` → sent to Google Slides

**What happens during Extraction:**
- Extractor reads `23.04pt` from Google Slides
- Currently returns `23.04` directly (NO conversion back!)

**The Problem:**
If you regenerate from extracted JSON, it becomes: `23.04 × 0.72 = 16.6pt` 😱

## The Fix

The extractor should **divide by SCALE** to convert back to virtual canvas coordinates. Currently, we only do this for `x`, `y`, `w`, `h`, but NOT for:
- `fontSize`

### 1. Unknown/Error Elements (Skip during generation)
Added explicit case handlers for `'unknown'` and `'error'` element types that safely skip them instead of logging warnings:
```javascript
case 'unknown':
case 'error':

```

### 2. Empty Text Styling (Table cells)
Wrapped the text insertion and styling in a check for non-empty text:
```javascript
if (text && text.length > 0) {
  // Insert text
  // Apply text styling
}
```

This prevents the "object has no text" API error when table cells are empty.

### How They Work:

```json
{
```

```json
{
  "type": "sheetsChart",
  "spreadsheetId": "abc123...",
  "chartId": 12345,
  "embedType": "LINKED",
  "x": 50, "y": 50, "w": 500, "h": 350
}
```
*Note: Requires the original spreadsheet to still exist and be accessible.*

**WordArt:**
```json
{
  "type": "wordArt",
  "text": "Hello World!",
  "x": 100, "y": 200, "w": 600, "h": 100
}
```
*Rendered as large bold centered text (API limitation).*

Great question! The error appeared because of the **new extraction workflow**:

**Before (manually authored JSON):**
- Shapes without text simply didn't have a `text` property
- OR `text` was only set when there was actual content
- The code worked fine because there were no edge cases

**Now (extracted from real presentations):**
1. The extractor pulls EVERY shape, including decorative ones
2. When extracting, `shape.getText().asString()` returns:
   - `""` for empty shapes
   - `"\n"` for shapes with just a trailing newline (Google Slides adds these)
3. These empty/whitespace-only strings were being included in the JSON with `"text": ""`
4. The generation code saw `element.text` existed and tried to style it

**The root cause:** Google Slides' API returns invisible characters (like trailing newlines) when you call `getText().asString()` on shapes that appear to have "no text". Our old check `text.trim().length > 0` didn't catch single-character whitespace that wasn't removed by `trim()`.

**The fix:** Using `/\S/.test(text)` - which checks for ANY visible non-whitespace character - handles all these edge cases properly.

This is actually a **sign of progress** - your extraction is now capturing complete presentations including decorative elements. The generation code just needed to be hardened to handle these real-world edge cases.

          "bold": false,
          "italic": false,
          "underline": false,
          "align": "left",
          "text": "Search, our key performance driver, experienced a steep decline in volume and CVR in Q2, which led to CPA inflation. \n \nQoQ BKWS impression was down by ~24%, Subs ~49% and CVR ~40%. With that, we saw a ~60% increase in BKWS CPA, concluding the quarter with a CPA of $22. \n\nWhen looking at the YoY trend, Google BKWS CPA peaked this Q2 while CVR dropped to the lowest point in seven quarters. CPC remains stable, which indicates the performance fluctuation was driven mainly by demand than competitions. \n\nOverall the 1H DR program was impacted greatly by COVID-19. YoY we saw a 150% increase in CPA and CVR declined by ~75%."

          "text": "Search, our key performance driver, experienced a steep decline in volume and CVR in Q2, which led to CPA inflation. \n \nQoQ BKWS impression was down by ~24%, Subs ~49% and CVR ~40%.           "bold": false,
          "italic": false,
          "underline": false,
          "align": "left",
          "text": "Search, our key performance driver, experienced a steep decline in volume and CVR in Q2, which led to CPA inflation. \n \nQoQ BKWS impression was down by ~24%, Subs ~49% and CVR ~40%. With that, we saw a ~60% increase in BKWS CPA, concluding the quarter with a CPA of $22. \n\nWhen looking at the YoY trend, Google BKWS CPA peaked this Q2 while CVR dropped to the lowest point in seven quarters. CPC remains stable, which indicates the performance fluctuation was driven mainly by demand than competitions. \n\nOverall the 1H DR program was impacted greatly by COVID-19. YoY we saw a 150% increase in CPA and CVR declined by ~75%."
